<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When using Zend_Mail-&gt;setParts(Zend_Mime_Message-&gt;getParts()) the message won't send a proper message; Zend_Mail_Transport_Abstract will throw a 'No body specified' exception. Zend_Mail stores the body parts  Zend_Mail-&gt;$_bodyHtml and  Zend_Mail-&gt;$_bodyText separated from the other body mime parts (Zend_Mime_Message-&gt;$_parts).</p>

<p>Either:
the Zend_Mail_Transport_Abstract should be able to handle mail without  Zend_Mail-&gt;$_bodyHtml and  Zend_Mail-&gt;$_bodyText being set 
or: 
the Zend_Mail-&gt;setParts() should take into account setting Zend_Mail-&gt;$_bodyHtml and Zend_Mail-&gt;$_bodyText body parts, although this is kind of a hilarious workaround.</p>

